HEADWORD: Woulfe bottle
<hw>Woulfe" bot`tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A kind of wash bottle with two or three necks; -- so called after
the inventor, Peter <xex>Woulfe</xex>, an English chemist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

